zing: inherit; color: inherit;\">HTML5 Browser Support</a>.</p><hr style=\"height: 0px; overflow: visible; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px;\"><h2 style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Arial, sans-serif; margin-top: 10px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px;\"><b>New Semantic Elements in HTML5</b></h2><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">Many web sites contain HTML code like: &lt;div id=\"nav\"&gt; &lt;div class=\"header\"&gt; &lt;div id=\"footer\"&gt;<br style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">to indicate navigation, header, and footer.</p><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">HTML5 offers new semantic elements to define different parts of a web page: &nbsp;</p><div style=\"box-sizing: inherit; width: 374px; float: left;\"><ul style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\"><li style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">&lt;article&gt;</li><li style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">&lt;aside&gt;</li><li style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">&lt;details&gt;</li><li style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">&lt;figcaption&gt;</li><li style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">&lt;figure&gt;</li><li style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">&lt;footer&gt;</li><li style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">&lt;header&gt;</li><li style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">&lt;main&gt;</li><li style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">&lt;mark&gt;</li><li style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">&lt;nav&gt;</li><li style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">&lt;section&gt;</li><li style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">&lt;summary&gt;</li><li style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">&lt;time&gt;</li></ul></div><div style=\"box-sizing: inherit; width: 260px; float: left; margin-bottom: 15px;\"><img alt=\"HTML5 Semantic Elements\" src=\"https://www.w3schools.com/html/img_sem_elements.gif\" width=\"219\" height=\"258\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; border-style: none;\"></div><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; clear: both;\"></p><div style=\"box-sizing: inherit; overflow: auto; text-align: center;\"><div id=\"div-gpt-ad-1493883843099-0\" data-google-query-id=\"COvsp4HJm9oCFRmQjgodsa8Ocg\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\"><br></div></div><h2 style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Arial, sans-serif; margin-top: 10px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px;\"><b>HTML5 &lt;section&gt; Element</b></h2><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">The&nbsp;<code class=\"w3-codespan\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: Consolas, &quot;courier new&quot;; font-size: 16.5px; color: crimson; background-color: rgb(241, 241, 241);\">&lt;section&gt;</code>&nbsp;element defines a section in a document.</p><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">According to W3C\'s HTML5 documentation: \"A section is a thematic grouping of content, typically with a heading.\"</p><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">A home page could normally be split into sections for introduction, content, and contact information.</p><div class=\"w3-example\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; background-color: rgb(241, 241, 241); padding: 0.01em 16px; margin: 20px 0px; box-shadow: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.16) 0px 2px 4px 0px, rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.12) 0px 2px 10px 0px !important;\"><h3 style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Arial, sans-serif; margin-top: 10px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px;\">Example</h3><div class=\"w3-code notranslate htmlHigh\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: Consolas, &quot;courier new&quot;; font-size: 16px; width: auto; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); padding: 8px 12px; border-left: 4px solid rgb(76, 175, 80); word-wrap: break-word; margin-top: 16px !important; margin-bottom: 16px !important;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: mediumblue;\">&lt;</span>section<span style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: mediumblue;\">&gt;</span></span><br style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;<span style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: mediumblue;\">&lt;</span>h1<span style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: mediumblue;\">&gt;</span></span>WWF<span style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: mediumblue;\">&lt;</span>/h1<span style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: mediumblue;\">&gt;</span></span><br style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;<span style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: mediumblue;\">&lt;</span>p<span style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: mediumblue;\">&gt;</span></span>The World Wide Fund for Nature (WWF) is....<span style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: mediumblue;\">&lt;</span>/p<span style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: mediumblue;\">&gt;</span></span><br style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: mediumblue;\">&lt;</span>/section<span style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: mediumblue;\">&gt;</span></span></div></div><hr style=\"height: 0px; overflow: visible; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px;\"><h2 style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Arial, sans-serif; margin-top: 10px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px;\"><b>HTML5 &lt;article&gt; Element</b></h2><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">The&nbsp;<code class=\"w3-codespan\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: Consolas, &quot;courier new&quot;; font-size: 16.5px; color: crimson; background-color: rgb(241, 241, 241);\">&lt;article&gt;</code>&nbsp;element specifies independent, self-contained content.</p><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">An article should make sense on its own, and it should be possible to read it independently from the rest of the web site.</p><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">Examples of where an&nbsp;<code class=\"w3-codespan\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: Consolas, &quot;courier new&quot;; font-size: 16.5px; color: crimson; background-color: rgb(241, 241, 241);\">&lt;article&gt;</code>&nbsp;element can be used:</p><ul style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\"><li style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">Forum post</li><li style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">Blog post</li><li style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">Newspaper article</li></ul><div class=\"w3-example\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; background-color: rgb(241, 241, 241); padding: 0.01em 16px; margin: 20px 0px; box-shadow: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.16) 0px 2px 4px 0px, rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.12) 0px 2px 10px 0px !important;\"><h3 style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Arial, sans-serif; margin-top: 10px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px;\">Example</h3><div class=\"w3-code notranslate htmlHigh\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: Consolas, &quot;courier new&quot;; font-size: 16px; width: auto; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); padding: 8px 12px; border-left: 4px solid rgb(76, 175, 80); word-wrap: break-word; margin-top: 16px !important; margin-bottom: 16px !important;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: mediumblue;\">&lt;</span>article<span style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: mediumblue;\">&gt;</span></span><br style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;<span style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: mediumblue;\">&lt;</span>h1<span style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: mediumblue;\">&gt;</span></span>What Does WWF Do?<span style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: mediumblue;\">&lt;</span>/h1<span style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: mediumblue;\">&gt;</span></span><br style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;<span style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: mediumblue;\">&lt;</span>p<span style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: mediumblue;\">&gt;</span></span>WWF\'s mission is to stop the degradation of our planet\'s natural environment,<br style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">&nbsp; and build a future in which humans live in harmony with nature.<span style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: med