w&quot;; font-size: 16.5px; color: crimson; background-color: rgb(241, 241, 241);\">&lt;article&gt;</code>&nbsp;elements containing&nbsp;<code class=\"w3-codespan\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: Consolas, &quot;courier new&quot;; font-size: 16.5px; color: crimson; background-color: rgb(241, 241, 241);\">&lt;section&gt;</code>&nbsp;elements.</p><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">You will also find pages with&nbsp;<code class=\"w3-codespan\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: Consolas, &quot;courier new&quot;; font-size: 16.5px; color: crimson; background-color: rgb(241, 241, 241);\">&lt;section&gt;</code>&nbsp;elements containing&nbsp;<code class=\"w3-codespan\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: Consolas, &quot;courier new&quot;; font-size: 16.5px; color: crimson; background-color: rgb(241, 241, 241);\">&lt;section&gt;</code>&nbsp;elements, and&nbsp;<code class=\"w3-codespan\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: Consolas, &quot;courier new&quot;; font-size: 16.5px; color: crimson; background-color: rgb(241, 241, 241);\">&lt;article&gt;</code>&nbsp;elements containing&nbsp;<code class=\"w3-codespan\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: Consolas, &quot;courier new&quot;; font-size: 16.5px; color: crimson; background-color: rgb(241, 241, 241);\">&lt;article&gt;</code>elements.</p><div class=\"w3-panel w3-note\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; padding: 0.01em 16px; margin-top: 16px; margin-bottom: 16px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 204); border-left: 6px solid rgb(255, 235, 59);\"><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">Example for a newspaper: The sport&nbsp;<code class=\"w3-codespan\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: Consolas, &quot;courier new&quot;; font-size: 16.5px; color: crimson; background-color: rgb(241, 241, 241);\">&lt;article&gt;</code>&nbsp;in the sport&nbsp;<strong style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">section</strong>, may have a technical&nbsp;<strong style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">section</strong>&nbsp;in each&nbsp;<code class=\"w3-codespan\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: Consolas, &quot;courier new&quot;; font-size: 16.5px; color: crimson; background-color: rgb(241, 241, 241);\">&lt;article&gt;</code>.</p></div><hr style=\"height: 0px; overflow: visible; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px;\"><h2 style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Arial, sans-serif; margin-top: 10px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px;\"><b>HTML5 &lt;header&gt; Element</b></h2><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">The&nbsp;<code class=\"w3-codespan\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: Consolas, &quot;courier new&quot;; font-size: 16.5px; color: crimson; background-color: rgb(241, 241, 241);\">&lt;header&gt;</code>&nbsp;element specifies a header for a document or section.</p><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">The&nbsp;<code class=\"w3-codespan\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: Consolas, &quot;courier new&quot;; font-size: 16.5px; color: crimson; background-color: rgb(241, 241, 241);\">&lt;header&gt;</code>&nbsp;element should be used as a container for introductory content.</p><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">You can have several&nbsp;<code class=\"w3-codespan\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: Consolas, &quot;courier new&quot;; font-size: 16.5px; color: crimson; background-color: rgb(241, 241, 241);\">&lt;header&gt;</code>&nbsp;elements in one document.</p><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">The following example defines a header for an article:</p><div class=\"w3-example\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; background-color: rgb(241, 241, 241); padding: 0.01em 16px; margin: 20px 0px; box-shadow: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.16) 0px 2px 4px 0px, rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.12) 0px 2px 10px 0px !important;\"><h3 style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Arial, sans-serif; margin-top: 10px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px;\">Example</h3><div class=\"w3-code notranslate htmlHigh\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: Consolas, &quot;courier new&quot;; fo