(38, 'HTML5 Migration', '<div class=\"w3-col l10 m12\" id=\"main\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; float: left; width: 1082.66px; transition: margin-left 0.4s; padding: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\"><h1 style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Arial, sans-serif; margin-top: 10px;\"><b>HTML5&nbsp;<span class=\"color_h1\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">Migration</span></b></h1><hr style=\"height: 0px; overflow: visible; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px;\"><h2 style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Arial, sans-serif; margin-top: 10px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px;\"><b>Migration from HTML4 to HTML5</b></h2><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">This chapter is entirely about how to&nbsp;<strong style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">migrate</strong>&nbsp;from&nbsp;<strong style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">HTML4</strong>&nbsp;to&nbsp;<strong style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">HTML5</strong>.</p><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">This chapter demonstrates how to convert an HTML4 page into an HTML5 page, without destroying anything of the original content or structure.</p><div class=\"w3-panel w3-note\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; padding: 0.01em 16px; margin-top: 16px; margin-bottom: 16px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 204); border-left: 6px solid rgb(255, 235, 59);\"><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">You can migrate from XHTML to HTML5, using the same recipe.</p></div><table class=\"html45\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; border: 1px solid grey; text-align: center; border-spacing: 15px; width: 1050.4px;\"><tbody style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\"><tr style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\"><th style=\"box-sizing: inherit; padding: 5px; text-align: center; width: 503.2px; font-size: 18px;\">Typical HTML4</th><th style=\"box-sizing: inherit; padding: 5px; text-align: center; width: 502.4px; font-size: 18px;\">Typical HTML5</th></tr><tr style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\"><td style=\"box-sizing: inherit; bo