pan><span style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: mediumblue;\">&gt;</span></span>SVG<span style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: mediumblue;\">&lt;</span>/text<span style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: mediumblue;\">&gt;</span></span><br style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">&nbsp; Sorry, your browser does not support inline SVG.<br style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: mediumblue;\">&lt;</span>/svg<span style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: mediumblue;\">&gt;</span></span></div></div><hr style=\"height: 0px; overflow: visible; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px;\"><h2 style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Arial, sans-serif; margin-top: 10px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px;\"><b>Differences Between SVG and Canvas</b></h2><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">SVG is a language for describing 2D graphics in XML.</p><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">Canvas draws 2D graphics, on the fly (with a JavaScript).</p><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">SVG is XML based, which means that every element is available within the SVG DOM. You can attach JavaScript event handlers for an element.</p><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">In SVG, each drawn shape is remembered as an object. If attributes of an SVG object are changed, the browser can automatically re-render the shape.</p><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">Canvas is rendered pixel by pixel. In canvas, once the graphic is drawn, it is forgotten by the browser. If its position should be changed, the entire scene needs to be redrawn, including any objects that might have been covered by the graphic.</p><hr style=\"height: 0px; overflow: visible; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px;\"><h2 style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Arial, sans-serif; margin-top: 10px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px;\"><b>Comparison of Canvas and SVG</b></h2><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">The table below shows some important differences between Canvas and SVG:</p><table class=\"w3-table-all notranslate\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; width: 1050.4px; border: 1px solid rgb(204, 204, 204); margin: 20px 0px;\"><tbody style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\"><tr style=\"box-sizing: inherit; border-bottom: 1px solid rgb(221, 221, 221);\"><th style=\"box-sizing: inherit; padding: 8px 8px 8px 16px; vertical-align: top; width: 524.8px;\">Canvas</th><th style=\"box-sizing: inherit; padding: 8px; vertical-align: top; width: 524.8px;\">SVG</th></tr><tr style=\"box-sizing: inherit; border-bottom: 1px solid rgb(221, 221, 221); background-color: rgb(241, 241, 241);\"><td style=\"box-sizing: inherit; padding: 8px 8px 8px 16px; vertical-align: top;\"><ul style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\"><li style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">Resolution dependent</li><li style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">No support for event handlers</li><li style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">Poor text rendering capabilities</li><li style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">You can save the resulting image as .png or .jpg</li><li style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">Well suited for graphic-intensive games</li></ul></td><td style=\"box-sizing: inherit; padding: 8px; vertical-align: top;\"><ul style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\"><li style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">Resolution independent</li><li style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">Support for event handlers</li><li style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">Best suited for applications with large rendering areas (Google Maps)</li><li style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">Slow rendering if complex (anything that uses the DOM a lot will be slow)</li><li style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">Not suited for game applications</li></ul></td></tr></tbody></table><hr style=\"height: 0px; overflow: visible; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px;\"><h2 style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Arial, sans-serif; margin-top: 10px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px;\"><b>SVG Tutorial</b></h2><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">To learn more about SVG,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.w3schools.com/graphics/svg_intro.asp\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: inherit;\">read our SVG Tutorial</a>.</p></div>', 3, 1, 0, '2018-03-31 14:13:42', '2018-04-02 19:26:33');
