(82, 'CSS Backgrounds', '<div class=\"w3-col l10 m12\" id=\"main\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; float: left; width: 940.828px; transition: margin-left 0.4s; padding: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\"><h1 style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Arial, sans-serif; margin-top: 10px;\"><b>CSS&nbsp;<span class=\"color_h1\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">Backgrounds</span></b></h1><div style=\"box-sizing: inherit; width: 908.828px; border: 1px solid gray; padding: 8px; background: url(&quot;mountain.jpg&quot;) rgb(225, 239, 187);\"><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-right: 150px;\">The CSS background properties are used to define the background effects for elements.</p><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">CSS background properties:</p><ul style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\"><li style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">background-color</li><li style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">background-image</li><li style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">background-repeat</li><li style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">background-attachment</li><li style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">background-position</li></ul></div><hr style=\"height: 0px; overflow: visible; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px;\"><h2 style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Arial, sans-serif; margin-top: 10px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px;\"><b>Background Color</b></h2><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">The&nbsp;<code class=\"w3-codespan\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: Consolas, &quot;courier new&quot;; font-size: 16.5px; color: crimson; background-color: rgb(241, 241, 241);\">background-color</code>&nbsp;property specifies the background color of an element.</p><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">The background color of a page is set like this:</p><div class=\"w3-example\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; background-color: rgb(241, 241, 241); padding: 0.01em 16px; margin: 20px 0px; box-shadow: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.16) 0px 2px 4px 0px, rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.12) 0p